event.title: BOE Gov Bailey Speaks
event.description: As the head of the Bank of England, the Governor's speeches can be influential in shaping market expectations and sentiment, particularly on matters related to monetary policy and interest rates. During these speeches, the Governor may discuss the BOE's economic outlook, provide insights into future policy decisions, or comment on recent economic developments.

event.title: ISM Manufacturing PMI
event.description: The Purchasing Managers' Index (PMI) is an economic indicator that measures the health of the manufacturing sector. It is calculated based on survey responses from purchasing managers at companies in the sector, assessing factors such as new orders, inventory levels, production, and employment.

event.title: RBNZ Gov Orr Speaks
event.description: As the head of the Reserve Bank of New Zealand, the Governor's speeches can be influential in shaping market expectations and sentiment, particularly on matters related to monetary policy and interest rates. During these speeches, the Governor may discuss the RBNZ's economic outlook, provide insights into future policy decisions, or comment on recent economic developments.

event.title: ISM Services PMI

event.title: CPI m/m
event.description: The Consumer Price Index (CPI) announcement is an essential economic indicator that affects currency valuation and the overall trading landscape. A significant portion of overall inflation comes from consumer prices, making the CPI announcement an important update for traders to stay informed on.

event.title: Cash Rate
event.description: The cash rate is the interest rate at which banks can borrow or lend funds on an overnight basis with the central bank. In many countries the Reserve Bank is responsible for setting the cash rate. Changes in the cash rate can have significant impacts on the economy and the financial markets.

event.title: RBA Rate Statement
event.description: The RBA Rate Statement is a regular announcement released by the Reserve Bank of Australia following its monthly monetary policy meeting. The statement provides an overview of the bank's decision regarding the official cash rate, which is the interest rate that banks pay to borrow money from the RBA.

event.title: Monetary Policy Statement
event.description: The Monetary Policy Statement (MPS) is a report published by a country's central bank, usually on a quarterly basis, that outlines the bank's monetary policy decisions and the rationale behind those decisions. The MPS typically includes an analysis of the current economic conditions, an assessment of risks and uncertainties, and projections for key economic indicators, such as inflation, employment, and GDP growth.

event.title: BOJ Press Conference
event.description: The BOJ Press Conference is a regular press conference held by the Bank of Japan (BOJ) after each policy meeting. The press conference provides an opportunity for the BOJ Governor and other senior officials to communicate the bank's monetary policy decisions, including any changes to interest rates or other policy tools. The press conference can also include updates on the bank's economic outlook, inflation forecasts, and other important indicators.

event.title: ADP Non-Farm Employment Change
event.description: The ADP Non-Farm Employment Change is a monthly report published by the US-based payroll processing company ADP that provides an estimate of the change in non-farm private sector employment during the previous month. The report is based on actual payroll data from over 400,000 US businesses and provides a useful early indication of the official non-farm payroll figures, which are released by the US Bureau of Labor Statistics (BLS) later in the month.

event.title: BOC Rate Statement
event.description: The BOC Rate Statement is a regular announcement released by the Bank of Canada (BOC) following its policy meetings. The statement provides an overview of the bank's decision regarding the overnight interest rate, which is the interest rate at which major financial institutions borrow and lend overnight funds among themselves.

event.title: Overnight Rate
event.description: The Overnight Rate is the interest rate at which major financial institutions borrow and lend overnight funds among themselves. The Overnight Rate is a key benchmark interest rate in many financial markets and is set by the central bank of the respective country. Changes in the Overnight Rate can have significant impacts on other interest rates, exchange rates, and financial markets.

event.title: JOLTS Job Openings
event.description: The JOLTS (Job Openings and Labor Turnover Survey) Job Openings report is a monthly release from the US Bureau of Labor Statistics (BLS) that provides an estimate of the number of job openings in the US economy during the previous month. The report includes data on job openings in various sectors of the economy, as well as information on hires, quits, and layoffs.

event.title: GDP m/m
event.description: The Gross Domestic Product (GDP) announcement is an important economic indicator that measures the broadest level of economic activity and serves as the primary gauge of the economy's health. As GDP increases, it typically signals economic growth, which can have a positive impact on the markets. Conversely, a decline in GDP can indicate an economic downturn and negatively affect the markets.

event.title: Employment Change
event.description: Employment Change is a monthly report published by various countries, which shows the net change in the number of people employed in the country during the previous month. It includes data on employment in various sectors of the economy, and can be an important indicator of economic growth or contraction.

event.title: Unemployment Rate
event.description: The Unemployment Rate is a monthly report published by various countries that shows the percentage of the labor force that is unemployed and actively seeking work. The MPS typically includes an analysis of the current economic conditions, an assessment of risks and uncertainties, and projections for key economic indicators, such as inflation, employment, and GDP growth.]]>

event.title: FOMC Meeting Minutes
event.description: <![CDATA[The Federal Reserve's Federal Open Market Committee (FOMC) meetings play a crucial role in the trading world. During these meetings, committee members vote on the nation's key interest rates which have a significant impact on the economy. FOMC members also use their public engagements to provide hints about future monetary policies, making these updates valuable for traders looking to make informed trading decisions.]]>

event.title: RBNZ Gov Orr Speaks
event.description: <![CDATA[As the head of the Reserve Bank of New Zealand, the Governor's speeches can be influential in shaping market expectations and sentiment, particularly on matters related to monetary policy and interest rates. During these speeches, the Governor may discuss the RBNZ's economic outlook, provide insights into future policy decisions, or comment on recent economic developments.]]>

event.title: Prelim GDP q/q
event.description: <![CDATA[The Gross Domestic Product (GDP) announcement is an important economic indicator that measures the broadest level of economic activity and serves as the primary gauge of the economy's health. As GDP increases, it typically signals economic growth, which can have a positive impact on the markets. Conversely, a decline in GDP can indicate an economic downturn and negatively affect the markets.]]>

event.title: Core PCE Price Index m/m
event.description: <![CDATA[The Core Personal Consumption Expenditures (PCE) Price Index is a measure of inflation in the United States that excludes the prices of food and energy. The index is released monthly by the Bureau of Economic Analysis.]]>

event.title: RBA Rate Statement
event.description: <![CDATA[The RBA Rate Statement is a regular announcement released by the Reserve Bank of Australia following its monthly monetary policy meeting. event.title: BOJ Press Conference
event.description: <![CDATA[The BOJ Press Conference is a regular press conference held by the Bank of Japan (BOJ) after each policy meeting. The press conference can also include updates on the bank's economic outlook, inflation forecasts, and other important indicators.]]>

event.title: ADP Non-Farm Employment Change
event.description: <![CDATA[The ADP Non-Farm Employment Change is a monthly report published by the US-based payroll processing company ADP that provides an estimate of the change in non-farm private sector employment during the previous month. The report is based on actual payroll data from over 400,000 US businesses and provides a useful early indication of the official non-farm payroll figures, which are released by the US Bureau of Labor Statistics (BLS) later in the month.]]>

event.title: BOC Rate Statement
event.description: <![CDATA[The BOC Rate Statement is a regular announcement released by the Bank of Canada (BOC) following its policy meetings. event.title: Overnight Rate
event.description: <![CDATA[The Overnight Rate is the interest rate at which major financial institutions borrow and lend overnight funds among themselves. The Overnight Rate is a key benchmark interest rate in many financial markets and is set by the central bank of the respective country. Changes in the Overnight Rate can have significant impacts on other interest rates, exchange rates, and financial markets.]]>

event.title: JOLTS Job Openings
